# Trendyol Integration Modules

## Module Map

| Module | Purpose | Endpoints |
|---|---|---|
| `catalog_lookup` | Resolve brandId, categoryId, attributeIds before product creation | getBrands, getBrandsByName, getCategoryTree, getCategoryAttributes, getCategoryAttributeValues |
| `product_onboarding` | Create new products via V2 API | createProducts |
| `product_update` | Update product metadata â€” title, images, attributes, variant fields, delivery | updateUnapprovedProducts, updateApprovedProductContent, updateApprovedProductVariant, updateApprovedProductDelivery |
| `inventory_price` | Update stock quantity and pricing only | updatePriceAndInventory |
| `product_lifecycle` | Archive, unlock, delete | archiveProducts, unlockProducts, deleteProducts |
| `batch_tracking` | Track async mutation results | getBatchRequestResult |
| `product_search` | Query and filter seller products | getProductBase, filterApprovedProducts, filterUnapprovedProducts |
| `buybox` | Competitive market state (optional) | getBuyboxInformation |

**`product_update` and `inventory_price` are two separate modules.**
- `product_update` â†’ metadata only (title, images, attributes, variant fields, delivery) â€” never price or stock
- `inventory_price` â†’ stock and price only â€” never metadata

## Module Presentation Rule
When presenting an integration plan, list every module by exact key name and purpose. Never collapse or group modules. `product_update` and `inventory_price` must always appear as separate items.

## Sequencing
- `catalog_lookup` always before `product_onboarding`
- `batch_tracking` required after every write
- `product_search` is the source of `contentId` for `updateApprovedProductContent`
- `buybox` is optional â€” excluded from plans by default

