## Attribute Format Difference

**createProducts**: `{ attributeId, attributeValueId: integer|null, customAttributeValue: string|null }`
**Update endpoints**: `{ attributeId, attributeValueIds: integer[], attributeValue: string }`

Never mix. Validator flags mixing with `WRONG_ATTRIBUTE_FORMAT_FOR_CREATE` / `WRONG_ATTRIBUTE_FORMAT_FOR_UPDATE`.

## TR vs GLOBAL

| | TR | GLOBAL |
|---|---|---|
| vatRate | Enum [0, 1, 10, 20] enforced | Country-specific, not enforced |
| storefrontCode | Always "1" | Seller-provided country code (e.g. "SA", "RO") |

## Common Endpoint Mistakes

| Wrong | Correct |
|---|---|
| `updateProduct` (V1 deprecated) | Appropriate V2 update endpoint |
| Content/variant endpoint for price/stock | `updatePriceAndInventory` |
| `updatePriceAndInventory` for metadata | `updateApprovedProductContent` or `updateUnapprovedProducts` |
| `filterProducts` (doesn't exist) | `filterApprovedProducts` or `filterUnapprovedProducts` |
| Parent category ID | Leaf (lowest-level) category ID |
| Partial attributes in content update | ALL attributes when any attribute changes |